Title: PlugOut Command
DM: 1
The DM plugout command is used to unload a plugin from loaded plugins.

<t t="Syntax:">/plugout [plugin]
<p><t t="See Also:">
^plugin^
^pluglist^
==========
Name: pluglist
Title: PlugList Command
DM: 1
The DM pluglist command is used to show currently loaded plugins. It will also show loadable plugins from the server's plugins directory.

<t t="Syntax:">/pluglist
<p><t t="See Also:">
^plugin^
^plugout^
==========
Name: shutdown
Title: Shutdown Command
DM: 1
The DM shutdown command is used to start a timed shutdown agent that shuts down the server in specified number of seconds.

<t t="Syntax:">/shutdown [seconds]
<p><t t="See Also:">
^shutdown_now^
==========
Name: shutdown_now
Title: Shutdown Now Command
DM: 1
The DM shutdown now command is used to shutdown the server instantly.

<t t="Syntax:">/shutdown_now
<p><t t="See Also:">
^shutdown^
==========
Name: resetmap
Title: Reset Map Command
DM: 1
The DM reset map command is used to reset a map the DM is currently located on. It will temporarily remove all players from the map, swap the map out, and reinsert the players.

<t t="Syntax:">/resetmap
==========
Name: create
Title: Create Command
DM: 1
The DM create command used to create almost any item.
<t t="NOTE: VERY DANGEROUS, USE WITH CAUTION!">

<t t="Syntax:">/create [number] [bonus] [archetype] [variable1] [value1] [variable2] [value2] ... 
==========
Name: addexp
Title: Add Exp Command
DM: 1
The DM add exp command is used to add exp to specified skill to a player.

<t t="Syntax:">/addexp [player name] [skill ID] [experience to add]
==========
Name: dm_stealth
Title: DM Stealth Command
DM: 1
The DM stealth command is used to allow a DM to become "stealthed" and invisible on /who list to anyone who is not a DM. On login his entering message will not be shown to other players. When other players message this DM they will get "No such player" message.

<t t="Syntax:">/dm_stealth
==========
Name: dm_light
Title: DM Light Command
DM: 1
The DM light command is used to make any map appear in daylight.

<t t="Syntax:">/dm_light
==========
Name: wizpass
Title: Wiz Pass Command
DM: 1
The DM wiz pass command is used to make a DM get stopped by walls and obstacles.

<t t="Syntax:">/wizpass
==========
Name: say
Title: Say Command
Autocomplete: 0
The say command is used to talk with other players on same map, interact with NPCs, activating teleporters and gates and other things.

This command does not require you to type anything before your message; you just write the message, and it gets said on the map you're located at.

<t t="Syntax:">[your message]

<t t="See Also:">
^shout^
^tell^
^reply^
==========
Name: motd_set
Title: Set MOTD Command
DM: 1
The DM MOTD set command can be used to change the Message of the Day from game. It is useful to use this for game events, as this message will be automatically displayed to players upon logging in. This command does not overwrite the "default" Message of the Day, but it inserts a custom one, which is then used instead of the default one.

<t t="Syntax:">To revert the original (default) Message of the Day:
/motd_set original

To set a custom Message of the Day:
/motd_set [message]
==========
Name: afk
Title: AFK Command
The AFK (Away From Keyboard) command is used to mark you as away. It will be displayed in the client as a "reminder" next to your name, and will appear in the who list for everyone to see.

<t t="Syntax:">/afk
==========
Name: dmsay
Title: DM Say Command
DM: 1
The DM say command can be used by DMs to chat among themselves. It is similar to commands like shout, say, etc, but it will appear in red, prefixed with [DM Channel] and only to other logged in DMs.

<t t="Syntax:">/dmsay [your message]
